properties.areaDesc: San Juan County; Western Whatcom County
properties.headline: Wind Chill Advisory issued January 13 at 1:30AM PST until January 13 at 11:00AM PST by NWS Seattle WA
properties.description:
* WHAT...Very cold wind chills near zero this morning.

* WHERE...San Juan County, including Stuart Island, Waldron
Island, Orcas Island, San Juan Island, Lopez Island, Blakely
Island, and Decatur Island and Lowlands of western Whatcom
County, including Point Roberts, Lummi Island, Bellingham, and
Sumas.

* WHEN...Until 11 AM PST this morning.

* IMPACTS...There may be a few areas of blowing snow where snow
fell overnight. Snow showers this morning will be light and
spotty. There is a danger of frostbite for exposed skin for
people outside this morning.
properties.instruction:
Use caution while traveling outside. Wear appropriate clothing, a
hat, and gloves.

NWSheadline: WIND CHILL ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 11 AM PST THIS MORNING... ...WINTER STORM WARNING IS CANCELLED
